  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Automotive Repair and Maintenance</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Motorcycle Mechanic</strong></li><li>Working Location: West, Bukit Batok</li><li>Working Hours: 6 Days, 10am – 8pm</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>$1500 - $2500</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform motorcycles services & maintenance such as diagnose, adjust, repair, overhaul motorcycles</li><li>Disassembles the engine or transmission, replace the defective part and then reinstall the rebuilt component</li><li>Fine tuning motorcycles</li><li>Other task as assigned</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of experience in a related field</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81298 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
